Q.   (No microphone.)
RORY McILROY:   Obviously, yesterday was a good day and got myself back into the tournament a little bit.   Today, today was tricky.   A lot of guys aren't going that low out there.   The wind was up a little bit.   The greens were slower today.   I felt like I was leaving a lot of putts short.   I'm not sure about the other guys out there but I felt like the greens were a lot slower today than they have been.   Maybe it's because I was playing in the morning the last two days, and because it's Bermuda they grow a little bit in the afternoon, but I just felt like I struggled to get the ball up to the hole on the greens. 
